- [ ] `pnpm run build` succeeds (Vite emits the bundle + `.d.ts` to `dist/`)
- [ ] `pnpm run build:tsc` succeeds (types compile)
- [ ] If you regenerated `emoji-lib.json`, the `TOTAL_EMOJIS` constant in `emojiLibJson.test.ts` is updated
- [ ] If you changed the public API, `docs/API_REFERENCE.md` and `README.md` are updated
- [ ] If you bumped a dep, `pnpm-lock.yaml` is committed
- [ ] No `console.*` calls in `src/`
- [ ] No `dist/` artifacts staged (gitignored)
- [ ] Commit message in English (conventional format)

## Skills, Commands & Subagents (AI Agent Tooling)

This repository ships with a `.agents/` directory (symlinked as `.claude/`) containing skill files, slash commands, and specialized subagents tuned for parser/library work. Full catalog: **[.agents/README.md](.agents/README.md)**.

**Slash commands (`.agents/commands/`):**

- `/regenerate-emoji-lib` ŌĆö Regenerate `src/lib/emoji-lib.json` from upstream `emojilib` + `unicode-emoji-json`
- `/add-special-case` ŌĆö Add a keyword include/exclude override to `EMOJIS_SPECIAL_CASES`
- `/write-tests` ŌĆö Author Vitest tests for a parsing bug or new feature
- `/fix-build` ŌĆö Diagnose a failing TypeScript / Vite / Vitest build
- `/bump-deps` ŌĆö Update one or more npm dependencies safely (respects `.ncurc.json`)
- `/release-npm` ŌĆö Walk through a manual release if CI is unavailable
- `/check-html-output` ŌĆö Verify the HTML output contract for a given input

**Skills (`.agents/skills/`):**

- `emoji-parser-conventions` ŌĆö Deep dive on the parse pipeline, regex caching, dual-export shape
- `emoji-data-pipeline` ŌĆö Step-by-step regeneration of the catalog from upstream
- `npm-publish-walkthrough` ŌĆö Full release flow including GitHub Actions internals
- `typescript-strict-style` ŌĆö TS rules enforced by `tsconfig.json` + Biome
- `pnpm-migration` ŌĆö Playbook for migrating npm ŌåÆ pnpm (Corepack pin, supply-chain guards, npmŌåÆpnpm routing, pnpm publish + tarball parity)

**Subagents (`.agents/agents/`):**

- `parser-architect` ŌĆö Decides where new logic lives and reviews public API shape
- `emoji-data-curator` ŌĆö Owns the catalog, keyword resolution, and special-case overrides
- `test-author` ŌĆö Writes Vitest tests, regression cases, and integration coverage
- `dependency-auditor` ŌĆö Reviews `package.json` changes, license/CVE checks, `.ncurc.json` exclusions
- `release-engineer` ŌĆö Owns Vite config, CI workflows, npm publish, GitHub release notes
- `doc-writer` ŌĆö Keeps `AGENTS.md`, `docs/`, and `README.md` synchronized with code

### How to Invoke Commands

| Agent               | Prefix       | Example                 |
| ------------------- | ------------ | ----------------------- |
| **Claude Code**     | `/` (native) | `/regenerate-emoji-lib` |
| **OpenAI Codex**    | `#`          | `#regenerate-emoji-lib` |
| **Cursor AI**       | `#`          | `#regenerate-emoji-lib` |
| **Gemini / others** | `#`          | `#regenerate-emoji-lib` |

> **Why `#` for non-Claude agents?** Most AI CLIs (Codex, Cursor) intercept `/` as their own system commands. Using `#` avoids interception. You can also write the command name in plain text: "run regenerate-emoji-lib".

When a command is invoked (via `/`, `#`, or by name), the agent MUST:

1. **Look up** the command in **[.agents/README.md](.agents/README.md)** to find its file
2. **READ** the linked command/skill file completely
3. **FOLLOW** its step-by-step instructions exactly
4. **DO NOT** improvise or skip steps ŌĆö the file IS the spec

## Conventional Commits

**Format:** `<type>: <description>`

**Types:** `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`, `perf`, `ci`, `build`

Examples:

- `feat: support :neckbeard: as a Slack dialect alias`
- `fix: parse :star: even when followed by VS-16 modifier`
- `chore: pin @twemoji/parser to 17.0.1 to avoid VS-16 regression`
- `build: emit ESM bundle alongside the Vite commonjs output`
- `docs: document EMOJIS_SPECIAL_CASES override workflow`
- `perf: cache parseToShortcode alternation regex`
- `ci: run biome:check as the single lint + format gate`

The CI release commit (`[­¤ż¢ DailyBot] New release to vX.Y.Z launched ­¤ÜĆ`) is reserved for the release workflow ŌĆö humans should not write it.

